Budget minded PC build with 'gamer' looks, decent performance, and non scalper pricing. Should excel at e-sports titles, and handle less frenetic or graphically intensive titles at up to 1080p mid/high settings. Right-click 'open image in new tab' for image and benchmark details.

Case was purchased used here on marketplace; CPU, fans, WIFI card, 2nd stick of RAM, and cooler were all brand new and sealed; remaining core components purchased open box 'like new'.

Details:
- Asus GeForce GTX 1650; 4GB GDDR5
- AMD Ryzen 5 3100; Zen 2, 65W, 3.6-3.9 GHz, Unlocked
- Cooler Master Hyper 212 Evo tower cooler with upgraded 120mm Deep Cool RF120 RGB fan
- Asus GL10DH B450 motherboard; PCIe Gen 3 x4 M.2 NVMe, USB 3, Gigabit LAN, - 16GB (2 x 8GB) DDR4-2666 RAM
- 512GB Intel 660p PCIe Gen 3 x4 NVME SSD
- Intel AX200 WIFi 6 and Bluetooth 5.1 with dual external antennas
- Cooler Master MB320L compact tower case with tempered glass side window, 'Dark Mirror' front panel, upgraded with 3 x 120mm Deep Cool RF120 RGB fans, externally mounted RGB controller
- AcBel 300W 80Plus Bronze PSU
- Windows 10 Home (OEM)

Message me to arrange a test drive (Whyte Ave/Old Strathcona neighborhood). Free/demo versions of benchmarks 3DMark, FurMark, and Heaven are installed, along with CPU-Z, GPU-Z, and HWInfo 64 so you can verify whatever you need to. Feel free to bring your own portable drive with game installs to test with - just let me know which game launcher(s) you'd like installed (Steam, Epic, etc.).

*Will not* part out, to dissuade crypto miners and scalpers. Not interested in trades. E-transfer (preferred) or cash if you are satisfied with your demo. Local sale only - **WILL NOT SHIP**
